John Charles Makurdi Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom has condemned the killing of a Catholic priest, Rev. Fr  David Tanko. The Rev Tanko was reportedly ambushed by gunmen on Thursday at Kufai Amadu in Takum Local Government Area of  Taraba State while traveling to  Takum for a peace meeting. Ortom in a statement issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Terver Akase, described the murder of the priest as shocking, painful and unfortunate. The governor commiserated with the government and people of Taraba State, particularly the Catholic Church over the sad incident. The statement quoted the governor in part, “Governor Ortom joins his Taraba counterpart, Architect Darius Ishaku, to call for an end to the bloodletting between the Jukun and Tiv in Taraba State. “The Governor says only peace can guarantee meaningful development.” Ortom urged security operatives to apprehend killers of Reverend Father Tanko to face the consequences of their actions. He consoled the family of the late Catholic priest and prayed that God grants him eternal rest.